  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Richard Allen sends autographs of &quot;the greatest man in Ireland, for such I hold Theobald Mathew to be.&quot; His name is also prefixed to the address from &quot;our&quot; [the Irish] nation. Teetotalers will be glad to have his autographs. The other autographs are from a forerunner of Father Mathew.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">On this stationery, there is an engraving of &quot;The Cove of Cork. Richard Allen comments about this engraving in a postscript: &quot;The little sketch at the head of this, was doubtless one of Father Mathew&apos;s early haunts -- It is a beautiful spot.</subfield>
